      <acqinfo id="aspace_c66d508df4879af9818700c43983944b">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of Ralph B. Little, 1982.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_36f1b6a8ef60f65e76df8edc3779a17f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The originals are in the security file and researchers are required to use electrostatic copies.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_922d5f697a9f769efb6957adc59eb25d">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright status for collection materials is unknown, though much of the material in this collection is likely in the public domain. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_05a26781dce85e0df71a24931e5b08f1">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Ralph B. Little Collection. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_f251f6cd944c8ee6a212ae7333a8564e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Ralph B. Little, Sr., was born around 1890. He received his veterinarian's degree from the University of Pennsylvania in 1914. In the following decades, he made significant advances in preventative veterinary medicine and died on July 27, 1965. Little's son, of the same name and also a doctor, appears to have inherited his father's collection of letters and autographs of presidents and other important historical figures.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_f1d2d6eb099c0498fcdb2edbe74cfb31">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Autograph collection of Ralph B. Little, containing prints and letters of American presidents and other public figures.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
